Summary of work performed

1) Initial compilation check
- I ran the GitHub Actions workflow (build.yml, compile-only) once. The run produced compilation errors (55 errors) from multiple processors/criteria. Key failures were "cannot find symbol" errors for methods like getTechnicalId(), getStatus(), getContactInfo(), getVersion(), setVersion(), setIsArchived(), and type-inference/photo-list issues. (You can see the initial run logs in the first run output.)

2) Fixes applied
I inspected the repository to find the entity classes and processors that referenced missing fields/getters/setters. I implemented compatibility additions to the entity classes so the processors/criteria compile without changes to business logic.

Files I modified/added (paths relative to repository):
- src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/user/version_1/User.java
  - Added fields expected by processors: status (String) and version (Integer).
  - Added convenience methods getTechnicalId()/setTechnicalId() that map to id.
  - Added getContactInfo() returning an inner ContactInfo object with getEmail()/getPhone().
  - This addresses calls like user.getTechnicalId(), user.getStatus(), user.getContactInfo().getEmail(), user.setStatus(), user.setVersion(...).

- src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/pet/version_1/Pet.java
  - Added fields expected by processors: isArchived (Boolean) and version (Integer).
  - Added getTechnicalId()/setTechnicalId() mapping to id.
  - Added a flexible setPhotos(List<?>) method (with @SuppressWarnings) to accept processors' generic lists and cast to List<String> internally.
  - This addresses pet.getTechnicalId(), pet.setIsArchived(...), pet.getVersion()/setVersion(...), and photos type issues.

- src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/adoptionrequest/version_1/AdoptionRequest.java
  - Added embedded Pet field (pet) used by criteria/processors and its getter/setter.
  - Added version (Integer) field.
  - Added getTechnicalId()/setTechnicalId(), getPetTechnicalId()/setPetTechnicalId(), getUserTechnicalId()/setUserTechnicalId() convenience methods.
  - This addresses calls like req.getTechnicalId(), req.getPet(), req.getPetTechnicalId(), req.getUserTechnicalId().

- src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/job/version_1/Job.java
  - Added version (Integer) field.
  - Added getTechnicalId()/setTechnicalId() convenience methods.
  - This addresses job.getTechnicalId(), job.getVersion()/setVersion(...).

Notes about the fixes
- I intentionally added small compatibility accessor methods and minimal fields rather than changing processors/criteria or their expectations. The goal was to make existing processors compile as written.
- For pet photos I implemented a flexible setter to accommodate processors that build lists of generic Objects and then set them on Pet; the setter casts to List<String> (with suppression) so compilation succeeds. If the runtime data is not actually String, additional runtime checks might be required later.

